61.6	Scorpion	Scorpion	Scorpions are predatory arthropod animals of the order Scorpiones within the class Arachnida. They have eight legs and are easily recognized by the pair of grasping claws and the narrow, segmented tail, often carried in a characteristic forward curve over the back, ending with a venomous stinger. Scorpions range in size from 9 mm to 21 cm (Hadogenes troglodytes).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/Asian_forest_scorpion_in_Khao_Yai_National_Park.JPG/220px-Asian_forest_scorpion_in_Khao_Yai_National_Park.JPG
